diff --git a/orderflow_services/prometheus_alerts_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.yml b/orderflow_services/prometheus_alerts_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.yml
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..85c39be
--- /dev/null
+++ b/orderflow_services/prometheus_alerts_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.yml
@@ -0,0 +1,47 @@
+groups:
+- name: cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1
+  rules:
+  - alert: ContCtxCalibratorStale
+    expr: time() - cont_ctx_calib_last_run_ts_seconds > 1800
+    for: 10m
+    labels:
+      severity: warning
+    annotations:
+      summary: "cont_ctx_window_calibrator appears stale"
+      description: "No successful recommendation loop for more than 30 minutes. Check worker logs and Redis connectivity."
+
+  - alert: ContCtxCalibratorLowSample
+    expr: sum by (symbol) (cont_ctx_calib_sample_n{window_ms="180000"}) < 20
+    for: 2h
+    labels:
+      severity: warning
+    annotations:
+      summary: "Low closed-trade sample for cont_ctx calibrator"
+      description: "Window 180000 has insufficient sample. Recommendation confidence may be unstable."
+
+  - alert: ContCtxCalibratorExpectancyNegative
+    expr: cont_ctx_calib_expectancy_r < 0
+    for: 30m
+    labels:
+      severity: critical
+    annotations:
+      summary: "Negative expectancy on recommended cont_ctx window"
+      description: "Recommended continuation context window has negative expectancy. Freeze auto-apply and rollback to baseline."
+
+  - alert: ContCtxCalibratorFalseBreakoutTooHigh
+    expr: cont_ctx_calib_false_breakout_rate > 0.22
+    for: 30m
+    labels:
+      severity: critical
+    annotations:
+      summary: "False breakout rate too high for cont_ctx window"
+      description: "Rescued continuation cohort is degrading. Consider reducing cont_ctx_valid_ms and inspect shadow outcomes."
+
+  - alert: ContCtxCalibratorExecTailWorse
+    expr: cont_ctx_calib_exec_p95_norm > 0.75
+    for: 30m
+    labels:
+      severity: critical
+    annotations:
+      summary: "Execution tail worsened after cont_ctx widening"
+      description: "exec_risk_norm p95 exceeds bounded limit for recommended window."
diff --git a/orderflow_services/runbook_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.md b/orderflow_services/runbook_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0eba01e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/orderflow_services/runbook_cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1.md
@@ -0,0 +1,55 @@
+# Runbook — cont_ctx_window_calibrator_v1
+
+## Purpose
+Post-analysis calibrator for `config:orderflow:{symbol}.cont_ctx_valid_ms`.
+It widens the continuation-context memory only when rescued continuation near-miss
+cohorts remain positive on shadow/paper outcomes.
+
+## Inputs
+- Redis Stream: `stream:ofc:cont_ctx_capture`
+- Shadow Stream: `stream:ofc:cont_ctx_shadow_signals`
+- Closed trades: `trades:closed`
+
+## Outputs
+- Prometheus endpoint on `CONT_CTX_CALIB_METRICS_PORT` (default `9137`)
+- Redis hash: `metrics:cont_ctx_window_calib:last:{symbol}`
+- Redis hash: `cfg:suggestions:cont_ctx_valid_ms:{symbol}`
+- Optional apply: `HSET config:orderflow:{symbol} cont_ctx_valid_ms <value>`
+
+## Safe defaults
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_MODE=RECOMMEND`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_MIN_SAMPLE=40`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_MIN_RESCUED=20`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_FALSE_BREAKOUT_MAX=0.22`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_EXEC_P95_NORM_MAX=0.75`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_MAX_STEP_MS=30000`
+- `CONT_CTX_CALIB_COOLDOWN_SEC=21600`
+
+## How to inspect
+```bash
+redis-cli HGETALL metrics:cont_ctx_window_calib:last:BTCUSDT
+redis-cli HGETALL cfg:suggestions:cont_ctx_valid_ms:BTCUSDT
+redis-cli XRANGE stream:ofc:cont_ctx_shadow_signals - + COUNT 5
+```
+
+## Manual apply
+```bash
+redis-cli HSET config:orderflow:BTCUSDT cont_ctx_valid_ms 150000
+```
+
+## Rollback
+```bash
+redis-cli HSET config:orderflow:BTCUSDT cont_ctx_valid_ms 120000
+redis-cli HSET config:orderflow:ETHUSDT cont_ctx_valid_ms 120000
+```
+
+## Disable auto-apply but keep observation
+```bash
+export CONT_CTX_CALIB_MODE=RECOMMEND
+```
+
+## Failure modes
+- No rows in `stream:ofc:cont_ctx_capture` → verify `CONT_CTX_CALIB_CAPTURE_ENABLE=1`
+- No closed-trade samples → verify shadow executor enriches `calib=1`,
+  `calib_kind=cont_ctx_window`, `candidate_window_ms`
+- Frequent `blocked_cooldown` → reduce apply cadence or increase confidence/sample thresholds
